\begin_layout Chapter*
About this book
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
What is this book?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The book aims to be a Master Handbook, including all the information necessary
 to be a successful leader in the Haslett band program.
 
\emph on
Don't let the size of this book scare you!
\emph default
 It simply serves the purpose of having the information necessary when needed.
 Although it would be highly beneficial to have the full content of this
 book understood and read, it is also meant for quick reference for information
 when it is needed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "chap:Fundamentals"
plural "false"
caps "true"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 of this book aims to stand as a 
\emph on
Manual of Style
\emph default
, a way to define how performers in the band execute maneuvers on the field,
 defining a ground-truth definition for each fundamental.
 I am adapting the term 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Manual of Style
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\emph on
 
\emph default
from Wikipedia's main styling guidelines documentation.
 If you are familiar with the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Fun with Fundamentals
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 document, you are familiar with the intention of this chapter.
 This chapter aims to be a revamped, updated, formalized version with full,
 complete information for every fundamental and marching maneuver, fleshed
 with figures and diagrams.
 This chapter should ideally be updated from year to year to adjust for
 additions or changes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
How do I use this book?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
This book is divided into several sections to divide fundamentals and marching
 maneuvers into separate levels and categories.
 If you are a Drum Major teaching fundamentals, you will want to ensure
 that the band is feeling comfortable with fundamentals in preceding sections.
 Teaching the band how to do a Roll Step
\emph on
 
\emph default
before teaching them how to do Attention may not go so well!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Each fundamental is broken down into its most important components.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

