\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
The band stops marking time when a leader shouts:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
BAN READY HALT!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The timing of the syllables forms a quarter, sixteenth, dotted-eighth, then
 a quarter.
 The band shall then respond, place the right foot down, and lift the left
 foot:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
LOCK AND CLOSE!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The band's response begins on beat 4 and is two eighth notes, followed by
 a quarter, landing on beat 1 on the next measure.
 The left foot is finally placed down on beat 1.
 See Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand vref
reference "subsec:Lock-and-Close"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 for more information.
\end_layout

