\begin_layout Subsection
Slow Turns
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\noun on
Slow Turns
\noun default
 are used to gradually rotate performers from facing one direction to another.
 They are less common than Flankings and are primarily used in fundamental
 block to rotate the band.
 However, they can appear in a show.
 Slow turns will always occur when at Attention.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Left Turn
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The band begins a 
\noun on
Left Turn
\noun default
 when a leader shouts:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
LEF TURN HO!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The timing of the syllables forms three even quarter notes of a 4/4 measure,
 landing on beats 1–3.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The band does not do anything on beat 4 of this measure.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On beat 1 of the next measure, the left foot is moved to be rotated 45º
 to the left.
 The left foot should pivot around the heel.
 The upper body should not rotate.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On beat 2, the right foot rotates about the heel to match the orientation
 of the left foot.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On beat 3, the left foot rotates another 45º to the left, resulting in a
 net rotation of 90º.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On beat 4, the right foot rotates another 45º to the left, matching the
 orientation of the left foot.
 The upper body 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

unlocks
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 from facing forwards and quickly rotates to the left to match the direction
 of the feet.
 The band finally responds on beat 4:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
LOCK!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Flex LilyPond
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

rhythm = 
\backslash
relative c'' {
\backslash
time 4/4
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
override NoteHead.style = #'cross
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

b4-.
 f-- b-- r | r2 r4 b4->}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

lyr = 
\backslash
lyricmode { LEF TURN HO! 
\backslash
markup 
\backslash
bold LOCK! }
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

