\begin_layout Subsubsection
Right Turn
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The band begins a 
\noun on
Right Turn
\noun default
 when a leader shouts:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
RIGHT TURN HO!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The timing of the syllables forms three even quarter notes of a 4/4 measure,
 landing on beats 1–3.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The band responds on beat 4 of this measure, picking up the left foot (like
 a mark time):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
AND!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On beat 1 of the next measure, the left foot is placed on the ground.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On beat 2, the right foot rotates about the heel 90º to the right.
 The upper body should not rotate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On beat 3, the left foot rotates 90º to the right, matching the orientation
 of the right foot.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On beat 4, the upper body 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

unlocks
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 from facing forwards and quickly rotates to the right to match the direction
 of the feet.
 The band finally responds on beat 4:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
LOCK!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
