\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Generated
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The generated drills are at various difficulties, getting increasingly harder
 with difficulty.
 
\emph on
Note: the generated drills asume an infinite field, so make sure there is
 enough space to complete the drill (or don't and throw off the band for
 elimination block since the band should respond AS YOU WERE if they cannot
 complete the drill!)
\emph default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Beginner
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The list of drills in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand vref
reference "tab:beginner-drills"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 lists every possible drill that follows the following set of rules:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Possible fundamentals: March
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Possible step sizes: 8:5
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
No double forwards/backwards marches
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
1–2 fundamentals
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

